# Documentation Maintenance

When major requirements, product behavior, or engineering conventions change, update the durable repo documentation instead of leaving the change only in chat.

## Keep In Sync

- `docs/product.md` for product goals, flows, and non-goals
- `AGENTS.md` for repo workflow, engineering conventions, and maintenance rules
- `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` for durable Cursor-facing rules that should mirror the same logic

## Update These Docs When Major Changes Land In

- product requirements
- core flows
- UX principles
- architecture or storage behavior
- auth/session behavior
- deployment/runtime assumptions
- repo conventions or workflow expectations
- testing strategy or automated validation expectations

## Avoid Drift

- Do not duplicate the same long guidance in multiple places unless the file has a distinct purpose
- Keep product truth in `docs/product.md`
- Keep workflow and coding rules in `AGENTS.md`
- Keep Cursor rules concise and aligned with the same durable decisions
